@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"
Introduction

The PPM Modules expand Opalpaint and Opal Utilities with the ability to load
and, if possible, save in PPM-Format.

Obviously you will need an Opalvision and installed software to use them.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"
Installation

Simply put 1. PPM.loader into Opalpaint:Loaders/
           2. PPM.saver into Opalpaint:Savers/

If you are not familiar with the Amiga the supplied Installation-Script will
do this for you.

If you got an older version of Opalpaint (<v2.1), you have to put Assignments
for "OpalLoaders:" & "OpalSavers:" in your User-startup:

              Assign OpalLoaders: Opalpaint:Loaders
              Assign OpalSavers:  Opalpaint:Savers

With newer versions of Opalpaint these Assigns are redundant and can be
removed.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "PPM-Loader" "PPM-Loader"
@TOC "MAIN"
PPM-Loader V1.70

The PPM-Loader loads P4 (black&white), P5 (gray) and P6 (rgb) variants of
the PPM-Format, special P5- & P6-Formats with less than 256 colors per plane
are also supported.
If you like to load an Image as Alpha or Stencil, you can do this by dese-
lecting all other Options in the Loader-Menu.

The PPM-Loader can be controlled via ARexx. Please see @{"ARexx-Interface" LINK "ARexx-Load"}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "PPM-Saver" "PPM-Saver"
@TOC "MAIN"
PPM-Saver V1.70

The PPM-Saver can save now the P5 (gray) and P6 (rgb) variants of the PPM-
Format. No Saving of Stencil-Data is supported.

If you like to save an Image as P5 (gray) variant, you can do this by dese-
lecting all other Options in the Loader-Menu (To save an Image as P5 an
image must be present in the Alpha-Channel).

The PPM-Saver can be controlled via ARexx. Please see @{"ARexx-Interface" LINK "ARexx-Save"}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ARexx-Save" "ARexx-Interface"
@TOC "MAIN"
ARexx-Interface of PPM-Saver

Here's some Example Code:

/*
** SaveasPPM.oprx
** $VER: SaveasPPM.oprx 1.00 (15 Mar 1999) by Rüdiger Schneider
** Saves the currently loaded Picture in PPM-Format
*/

OPTIONS RESULTS
ADDRESS 'OpalPaint_Rexx'

SaveComponents Image   /* Save Imagedata */
Saver PPM
Save "dh0:OutPic.ppm"

EXIT

/*
** SaveasPGM.oprx
** $VER: SaveasPGM.oprx 1.00 (15 Mar 1999) by Rüdiger Schneider
** Saves the currently loaded Alpha-Picture in PGM-Format
*/

OPTIONS RESULTS
ADDRESS 'OpalPaint_Rexx'

SaveComponents Alpha   /* Save Alphadata new in V1.70 */
Saver PPM
Save "dh0:OutPic.pgm"

EXIT
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ARexx-Load" "ARexx-Interface"
@TOC "MAIN"
ARexx-Interface of PPM-Loader

You should never use this:

/*
** LoadPPM.oprx
** $VER: LoadPPM.oprx 1.00 (10 Feb 1997) by Rüdiger Schneider
** Loads only Pictures in PPM-Format
*/

OPTIONS RESULTS
ADDRESS 'OpalPaint_Rexx'

Loader PPM
Load "dh0:InPic.ppm"

EXIT



Instead you should use this:

/*
** LoadsPPMtoo.oprx
** $VER: LoadsPPMtoo.oprx 1.00 (10 Feb 1997) by Rüdiger Schneider
** Loads all kind of Pictures including PPM
*/

OPTIONS RESULTS
ADDRESS 'OpalPaint_Rexx'

Loader Intelligent
Load "dh0:InPic.ppm"

EXIT
@ENDNODE

@NODE "PPM-Format" " About the PPM-Format "
About the PPM-Format

The PPM-Format is a simple File-Format very common on UNIX-Machines.

Advantage:     - Highly portable between different Computer-Platforms

Disadvantage:  - No compression of Picture-Data, so Files are very big
                 and slow to read and write.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Tips" "Tips and Tricks"
Tips and Tricks

I suggest that you only install Loaders & Savers you really need, because
they occupy memory even if unused.

If you want the list (which appears, when you hit the right mouse button
over the Load- or Save-Gadget) of currently available Loaders & Savers to
be alphabetically sorted, you just have to open "Opalpaint:Loaders/", copy
all loaders to a save location, delete all loaders in "Opalpaint:Loaders",
and copy them alphabetically (first GIF.loader, then PPM.loader ...) back
into "Opalpaint:Loaders/".
@ENDNODE

@NODE "History" "Version History"
Version History

Version 1.2  :    Initial Release

Version 1.30 :  - Reduced Size of Loader & Saver.

                - Now programs try to allocate Memory to hold
                  20 lines, and if this fails, try again
                  with less lines (old Versions simply quit).

                - PPM.saver: Fixed serious bug, causes machine
                             to crash if you try to save out a
                             PPM with less than 20 lines.

                - PPM.loader: Fixed serious bug, can't load
                              PPM with less than 20 lines.

Version 1.40 :  - Rewritten big parts of the programs in
                  Assembler.

                - PPM.loader: added Support for P4-Bitmaps.

                - Speed Increasement: about 10 percent.

                - Reduced Size of Loader & Saver.

Version 1.50 :  - Added ability to load Images created
                  by PersonalPaint.

                - Better loading of corrupted files, you will
                  only loose the line the corruption starts and
                  following (previous versions 20 lines).

                - Bugfix for Saver: Crashing if removed from mem
                  using RemoveLSI fixed.

Version 1.60 :  - Smaller Code.

                - Bugfix for Loader: Crashing if multiple comment
                  lines appear fixed.

                - Loader now supports PGM's & PPM's with less than
                  8 colors.

Version 1.70 :  - Smaller Code.

                - Saver now supports saving of PGM's (gray).
@ENDNODE

